OL,3,CCar cloning: What is the crime and why
OL,4,Cis it on the rise?
OL,6,FIt is difficult to know if a car has
OL,7,Fbeen cloned until the police are
OL,8,Falerted to criminal activity involving
OL,9,Fthat vehicle.
OL,11,FDrivers might start getting penalty
OL,12,Fnotices about traffic offences or
OL,13,Fcongestion charges that are not
OL,14,Frelated to them.
OL,16,FThe police urge drivers to contact
OL,17,Fthem if their number plates are
OL,18,Fstolen, and if they receive suspicious
OL,19,Fparking fines.
